HOLDING LEFTIST JUDGES ACCOUNTABLE:
The U.S. Senate will soon take up a bill to strip the country&rsquo;s 677 federal district judges of the power to issue nationwide injunctions, said Senate Majority Whip John Barrasso, R-Wyoming.

Under the bill, injunctions from judges at the district level could pertain only to the parties before the court. There is an exception for class-action lawsuits, but essentially under JRCA, judges could not halt actions by President Donald Trump's administration on a national level.

Barrasso touted the bill on the Senate floor last week, saying &ldquo;partisan, unelected, district court judges&rdquo; are trying to &ldquo;micromanage the president of the United States.&rdquo;
